text=!!Boards, Directors, and Appointed Executive%0a%0a# %25outline%25 [[#executive]]Appointed Executive%0a## The Executive may, from time to time as needed, appoint individuals to assist them in their Office.%0a## The term of Office for Appointed Executive is up to the discretion of the Executive Officer in question, but it may not exceed the term of Office of that Officer.%0a%0a# [[#directors]]Directors%0a## All Directors must be Social members of the [[Bylaws.Definitions#society|Society]].%0a## Directors will be appointed by the Executive Officer to whom they report, subject to ratification by [[Bylaws.Definitions#council|Council]].%0a## Directors may be removed by the Executive Officer to whom they report, subject to ratification by [[Bylaws.Definitions#council|Council]].%0a## In the event that no one is appointed as Director of a board, the Executive Officer to whom that Director would report shall discharge all necessary duties of the Director.%0a## Directors shall have a term of Office of one term, but may be re-appointed if otherwise eligible.%0a## The Director of each Board shall:%0a### convene meetings of the Board;%0a### be the sole representative of the Board on Council and be responsible for all correspondence on behalf of the Board;%0a### recommend and administer all budgets for the programs and activities of the Board;%0a### maintain the record binder for the Board;%0a### maintain at least one office hour per week;%0a### prepare a written report at the end of each term outlining the activities of the Board over the past term of the Board to be filed in the record binder for that directorship for future reference;%0a### in the event of an Annual General Meeting of the Society, prepare and present a report of the activities of the Board over the last year; and%0a### report to [[Bylaws.Definitions#council|Council]] on the status of the Board.%0a
